Seems essentially duplicate of bug 1147069.
So is any Fedora gimp package maintainer doing some activity on reports like this ?

And seems to be 'well' ignored by Debian as well:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=809064

Created attachment 1168824 Valgrind trace from crashing
This valgrind trace has not full debug info - but it seems something wrong is with gegl to touch wrong memory.
Anyone who has more time - enjoy and provide better fix - meanwhile I'm done with mem-leaking hotfix...
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 25 development cycle. Changing version to '25'.

Sorry for the lack of response.
As this issue affects the main program, I don't want to introduce memory leaks rather than fixing the root cause (and upstream, too, probably ;). Meanwhile a new upstream version came out -- 2.8.18 -- can you reproduce the issue there?

Well I've no idea how to fix it properly - it would took me significant amount of time to properly analyze it.
Surely the gimp-2.8.18-1.fc25.x86_64 is crashing still the same way and it's very easy to test -
- click on 'cage' deformation. - select couple points (i.e. create 3-point triangle) - finalize deformation by pressing 'Enter' (do not need to even deform anything)
Well - having very 'minor' memleak compared with some major portions of memory which is needed for image manipulation isn't that bad - especially compared with 'coredump' and losing whole work.
Anyway - I do have my own build where 'cage' work - so possibly other user may 'enjoy' the fix as well.
I've not tried to build latest gimp git HEAD as it seems to be untrival on current Rawhide as lots of required dep packages are not yet available for Rawhide - so further local building would be needed....
I've also not checked if the possible bug is in some gimp used library or it's API misuse on gimp side.
Hmm. I can only seem to reproduce this on Rawhide, not F-24.

Hmm - I'm always on rawhide...
And installing older version of Gimp was not solving issue on my box...
I'm assume that "something else" changed then, i.e. some library used by GIMP. Do you still see the issue?

So just tried on my rawhide:
gimp-libs-2.8.18-1.fc25.x86_64 gimp-2.8.18-1.fc25.x86_64
gegl-0.2.0-29.fc25.x86_64
And it WORKS :) - no crash after return press.
So as of now - the issue appeared to be fixed by some lib upgrade.
(I may assume it could be 'gegl' - but I've no real idea - could be gtk lib as well)
